    <abstract>
      <para>
      Learn how to debug and troubleshoot &nm; installation and configuration issues.
      </para>
    </abstract>
  </info>
  <section xml:id="networkmanager-nmcli-troubleshoot-verify-status">
    <title>Network is not running</title>
    <para>Ensure that &nm; is enabled:</para>
    <screen>systemctl status NetworkManager</screen>
    <para>To restart &nm; if it is inactive:</para>
    <screen>&prompt.sudo; systemctl restart NetworkManager</screen>
    <para>To enable &nm;:</para>
    <screen>&prompt.sudo; systemctl enable NetworkManager</screen>
    </section>
    <section xml:id="networkmanager-nmcli-troubleshoot-wifi-connection">
    <title>Wi-Fi connectivity issue</title>
    <para>Verify the connection and reconnect to the network.</para>
    <itemizedlist>
      <listitem>
        <para>Verify the SSID:</para>
        <screen>
nmcli device wifi rescan
nmcli device wifi list
</screen>
      </listitem>
      <listitem>
        <para>Reconnect to the Wi-Fi network:</para>
        <screen>nmcli device wifi connect <replaceable>SSID</replaceable> password <replaceable>PASSWORD</replaceable></screen>
      </listitem>
    </itemizedlist>

    </section>

</topic>
